  Singmaster's Conjecture

  Domain: mathematics
  ID: opa.mathematics.combinatorics.singmasters-conjecture
  Status: Open

  In Pascal's triangle, each number appears some number of times. The number 1 appears infinitely often (it borders both sides), but every other number seems to appear only finitely many times. The conjecture says there is a universal upper bound on how many times any number greater than 1 can appear.
-/

